### Required `.env` additions (each teammate needs these locally â€” not committed)

`backend/.env`:
```
SUPABASE_URL=<same value as EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, no prefix>
PASSWORD_RESET_TOKEN_SECRET=<random string â€” generate with the command below>
```

Generate a secret:
```powershell
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

SMTP is optional in dev â€” if unset, the OTP prints to the backend console instead of emailing:
```
[email] SMTP not configured â€” password reset OTP for user@example.com: 1234
```
To send real emails, also add: `SMTP_HOST`, `SMTP_PORT`, `SMTP_USER`, `SMTP_PASS`, `SMTP_FROM`.

### Bugs hit + fixes (Windows / Expo dev client)

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| "Network request failed" calling backend from phone | `frontend/.env` had `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` set to `localhost` | Use PC's LAN IP instead: `ipconfig` â†’ IPv4 under Wi-Fi adapter â†’ `http://192.168.x.x:4000` |
| Still failed after fixing IP | Duplicated variable name typo: `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL= EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://...` | Fix to single `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.x.x:4000`, restart with `npx expo start --dev-client -c` (cache clear â€” env vars are baked into the bundle) |
| Phone browser also couldn't reach `192.168.x.x:4000` | Windows Firewall blocking inbound port 4000 | `New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName "Node Dev Server 4000" -Direction Inbound -LocalPort 4000 -Protocol TCP -Action Allow` (run as Administrator) |
| `verify-otp` â†’ "Password reset is not configured" (503) | Missing signing secret; code checks for `PASSWORD_RESET_TOKEN_SECRET`, `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET`, or `JWT_ACCESS_SECRET` â€” none present | Added `PASSWORD_RESET_TOKEN_SECRET` to `backend/.env` |
| `reset-password` â†’ "SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are required" | Only `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` existed (frontend-style); backend admin code needs plain `SUPABASE_URL` | Added `SUPABASE_URL=<same value, no prefix>` |

